                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 23700/17.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Hill</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Extract.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-04-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 22, 1910</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Referring to department’s April 16, Ambassador Hill says formalities for transit
                    from Germany are the same as extradition from that country, and that an agent
                    can not accompany fugitive on board German vessel or through Germany.</p>
            </div>
